ENTRY            M1027   20260123   20260302   20260302       M144
SUBENT        M1027001   20260123   20260302   20260302       M144
BIB                 15         53
TITLE      Excitation of 180Hf-m with (gamma,p) reaction.
AUTHOR     (V.A.Zheltonozhsky,A.M.Savrasov,M.V.Zheltonozhskaya,
           A.P.Chernyaev)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,57,121,2021)
           #doi:10.1140/epja/s10050-021-00432-9
INSTITUTE  (4UKRIJD,4RUSMOS)
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Induced beta-delayed gamma-activity measured.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Gamma spectrometers based on the three HPGe-
            detectors which have an energy resolution of 1.8-2.0
            keV at the 1332.5 keV peak of 60Co and an efficiency
            of 15-40% at 1332.5 keV relative to 3" x 3" NaI(Tl)
            detector.
MONITOR    ((73-TA-181(G,N)73-TA-180,,SIG)+
           (73-TA-181(G,N+P)72-HF-179,,SIG))
           The flux of bremsstrahlung g-rays was calculated using
            the well studied 181Ta(g,n)180Ta-g reaction on the
            same target.
MONIT-REF  (M0850003,V.V.Varlamov+,J,PAN,76,1403,2013)
CRITIQUE   The reaction of M0850003 could be interpreted as
            181Ta(g,n)180Ta, but not as 181Ta(g,n0)180Ta-g.
ANALYSIS   Gamma-quanta energy spectrum lines data.
           For adaptation of the experimental spectra the
            Winspectrum program was used. This program permits
            the user to process the spectra in definite time
            controls, therefore, enabling the identification of
            the nuclides from the energies of the g-rays and
            their half-lives.
           To obtain the population for the isomeric state with
            IPi = 8- for the 181Ta(g,p)180Hf-m reaction at
            Eg-max = 20 MeV the net peak area of 215.3 keV g-rays
            which depopulated the excited level of 180Hf-m was
            measured.
           To get the population of 180Hf-m at Eg-max = 40 and
            55 MeV the photo-peak activity of 443.1 keV g-rays
            were determined.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical errors.
COMMENT    For the first time the flux-weighted average yields
            of 180Hf-m in (g,p) reaction were measured by
            activation and off-line g-ray spectrometric
            technique at the bremsstrahlung end-point energies
            of 20, 40 and 55 MeV.
           Using weighted-average fluxes of bremsstrahlung
            gamma-rays the weighted-average reaction cross
            sections could be obtained and therefore only
            integrated cross sections are in fact measured in
            experiments.
STATUS     (TABLE,,V.A.Zheltonozhsky+,J,EPJ/A,57,121,2021)
            Data from the Table 1.
HISTORY    (20210803C) Data were compiled at the Russia MSU SINP
            CDFE by V.Varlamov.
           (20211011A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: REL-REF deleted.
           (20260123U) Corrected by VV and SD: STATUS.
